"Sharon Anderson of KCMO,""Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2025"",""I originally ordered these (the first time) on Saturday, February 1st, 2025, and received them via Next Day Service on Sunday, February 2nd, 2025. I tried to charge them (as instructed), but unfortunately, they would not charge. The red indicator light went out after only about 30 seconds. I did test the Audio Cable that was included and it worked fine. Since my job entails transcription, it was great and fantastic that I could hear what I was transcribing with the utmost """"clarity"""" are they are simply spectacular in that respect. Also, the Noise Cancellation Feature is also a definite """"plus"""" because it literally blocks all of the noise that happens to be around you at any given time, so, you can actually hear through these Headphones (as stated on the description) without any background noise. Due to the fact that I do love these Headphones, I did order another set of them yesterday (February 3rd, 2025) and I received them once again, via Next Day Morning Delivery which was February 4th, 2025. Obviously, I am returning the first ones that I ordered expeditiously, and I have already tried out the pair that I got (today) and as far as charging them, they are """"not faulty or defective."""" The red light actually stayed on for the period of the 3-hour charge. So, to wrap this review up, I highly recommend anyone to purchase these Headphones for your listening pleasure (whatever it may be), albeit for music, work purposes or the like and hopefully if you order a pair and receive them, they will work and perform normally. Good luck!"""		
"tapu,""Reviewed in the United States on September 1, 2020"",""UPDATE 11/11/20: With the release of firmware 2.0.7 these have become usable for conference calls on Windows 10. The issue with initial syllables getting cut-off appears to be fixed and overall I have reports when using Skype and Zoom from my co-workers is that I now sound as good as (or maybe even a bit better than) other co-workers using Bose NC 700 headphones. According to Sony's release notes this firmware update is only supposed to address connection stability on Windows. I have increased my rating to 4 stars."		
		
