"Michael J. Mclaughlin,""Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2025"",""I didn’t think I would like the Sony 1000MX4’s, but being a headphone junkie and former radio DJ, I take my cans seriously. I love my Oppo PM-3’s, you can’t get them anymore, but they were well worth the $400 that I paid, same with my Sennheisers and Grados and a bunch of others….but these 1000MX4’s are really a fun set to own. The Bluetooth is a bonus, it’s software offers a few choices to custom design your preferred settings. The bass is tight, punchy in fact…even without the noise cancelling turned on…and the higher end rolls off a bit, but it is really pleasant to the ear. Even without the noise canceling, I can drown out exterior noise easily. I used to love Sony products, but in recent years, I always thought they dropped off a bit… well, I was wrong… and it’s OK to be wrong. These headphones are perfect for walking and enjoying your music."		
		
